option.name: content
option.value:
Du er min AI-parutvikler. Følg alltid disse prinsippene:
Mål - Bygg endringer i tråd med Domain-Driven Design (DDD), SOLID, Clean Code. - Praktiser Controller–Service–Repository som adaptere rundt domenet (ikke legg domene-logikk i controller/repository). - Skriv idiomatisk Kotlin, Spring Boot, Hibernate/JPA.
DDD - Bruk Ubiquitous Language. Domenemodeller skal ha atferd, ikke bare data (unngå anemisk domenemodell). - Entiteter har identitet + invarianter; Value Objects er immutable; Aggregater håndhever regler via Aggregate Root. - Application Service = use cases (orkestrerer domenet, ingen infrastrukturdetaljer). - Infrastruktur (REST, JPA, eksterne klienter) er adaptere som implementerer porter definert av applikasjons-/domenelag.
SOLID - SRP: Hver klasse/metode har én grunn til endring. - OCP/LSP: Utvid via abstraksjoner og pålitelig substitusjon. - ISP: Små, målrettede interfaces (port/grensesnitt per klient/behov). - DIP: Domene/applikasjon avhenger av abstraksjoner, infrastruktur avhenger av disse.
Clean Code - Klare, presise navn; små funksjoner; minst mulig public setters; immutable VOer. - Unngå duplisering; preferer komposisjon fremfor arv; sjekk invarianter tidlig. - God feilhåndtering med meningsfulle unntak; ingen «magiske tall/strings».
Arkitektur - Controller → Application Service (use case) → Domain (Aggregat) → Repository (port) → Repository-impl (JPA). - Controller mapper DTO ⇄ Command/Result; valider inn/ut; ingen forretningslogikk. - Repositories returnerer Aggregates/VOer (ikke JPA-entities direkte til controller).
Testing - TDD der det gir verdi. Unit-test domene/use cases uten database. - Repository-impl testet med Testcontainers (Postgres). Integrasjonstester med WireMock/MockWebServer. - F.I.R.S.T.-prinsippene for tester.
Kvalitet - Skriv KDoc (ikke @author/@since). Ingen bruks-eksempler i doc. - Oppdag og adresser code smells løpende. - Behold eksisterende kontrakter/stabile APIer; marker breaking changes tydelig.
Leveranser - Når du foreslår kode: vis bare nødvendige klasser/metoder for endringen (ingen overflødig «demo»-kode). - Når valgene er tvetydige: velg det enkleste designet som respekterer reglene over.

option.name: content
option.value: Skriv JavaDoc kort og presist. - Ingen eksempel-kode. - Ikke bruk @author/@version/@since. - Ingen HTML-tags. - Ikke dokumenter felt/properties individuelt. - Beskriv hensikt, pre-/postbetingelser og viktige invarianter.

task.summary: chore(cors): update allowed origins to use port 5175 for local and networked access

feat(consultants): add consultant sync and CV query functionalities
- Introduced `/api/consultants/sync` controller with manual sync endpoints (all consultants or individual). - Added `/api/consultants/with-cv` endpoints for retrieving consultants with nested CV structures, supporting pagination and filtering by active CVs. - Implemented `ConsultantPersistenceService` and `ConsultantWithCvService` for handling persistence and querying logic. - Expanded CV repositories with additional entity support for detailed CV data management. - Enhanced Maven configuration to include no-arg plugin setup for JPA compatibility. - Liquibase: updated CV columns to text type for longer descriptions.

feat(skills): refactor skill aggregation, enhance requirements analysis, and optimize CORS configs
- Refactored `ConsultantEntity.skills` to use `String` over enums for easier maintainability. - Added `ProjectSkillFetcher` for aggregating project-related skills and merged results with consultant skills. - Enhanced `ProjectRequestAnalysisService` to parse and persist requirements efficiently, including title/summary derivation. - Moved mappers to a standalone `ProjectRequestMappers` class for better modularity. - Improved CORS configuration to allow all origins (development mode) and set max-age for preflight requests. - Updated associated DTOs, repositories, and tests to align with the new skill aggregation logic. - Introduced Liquibase changeset to extend skill column length to 255 characters.

feat(config/tests): refine CORS setup and improve Maven test structure
- Added `@Profile` annotations for local, test, and integration environments in `WebConfig` and introduced `IntegrationWebConfig` for integration-specific CORS settings. - Updated Maven Surefire and Failsafe configurations to include/exclude test patterns explicitly. - Enhanced test execution flexibility by separating unit and integration test handling. - Documented Maven test structure and execution commands in WARP guide.

feat(skills): normalize skill storage and update related services
- Added `SkillEntity`, `ConsultantSkillEntity`, and `CvProjectSkillEntity` for normalized skill storage. - Updated `ConsultantEntity` to remove direct skill storage and reference `ConsultantSkillEntity`. - Modified `SkillsService` to use domain `SkillService` for skill aggregation. - Refactored `ConsultantWithCvService` for streamlined CV and skill querying. - Introduced a new Liquibase changeset to migrate skills structure. - Enhanced tests to cover new skill-related functionalities and domain services.

feat(skills): remove `acquiredInProject` field, enhance skill aggregation logic, and update related tests
- Dropped `acquiredInProject` from `SkillEntity` and domain model for simplification. - Updated `SkillsService` to aggregate skills by merging consultant-level and project-level data. - Introduced handling for legacy skill tables in skill aggregation. - Adjusted tests, DTOs, and repositories to align with updated skill structure. - Added a Liquibase changelog to remove the `acquiredInProject` column from the database schema. - Refactored `GoogleGeminiEmbeddingProvider` to handle large text payloads with improved chunking logic and semantic task support.

feat(consultants): introduce advanced search capabilities with semantic and relational criteria
- Added relational search with `RelationalSearchCriteria` supporting filters like skills, quality score, and active CVs. - Implemented semantic search using embeddings via `SemanticSearchCriteria` and `pgvector`, allowing natural language queries. - Developed `ConsultantSearchService` and `ConsultantSearchRepository` for combining relational and semantic search operations. - Introduced `/api/consultants/search` and `/api/consultants/search/semantic` endpoints in `ConsultantSearchController` for search functionality. - Added comprehensive unit tests for service and controller layers to ensure robust implementation.

docs: localize README, improve examples, and refine implementation details
- Translated documentation to Norwegian for consistency within the project. - Enhanced structured and semantic search examples with clear JSON samples. - Detailed architecture, system requirements, and local setup instructions for better onboarding. - Integrated best practices for environment variable configuration and updated database setup steps. - Streamlined API endpoint examples, emphasizing search scenarios and embedding functionality. - Added logging improvements and safeguards in Repository/Service for enhanced traceability.
